Hi, I’ve been working on updating our PTA community app and I’m running into some issues with the main module. I’ve been tweaking some event scheduling functionality in my main Python file (located at /home/erin_johansson/projects/PTAapp/src/main.py), and I’m not sure why the event notifications aren’t triggering as expected. I’ve pasted a snippet of the code below:

----------------
# main.py

def schedule_event(event_details):
    # Code to schedule event
    if event_details.get('notify'):
        send_notification(event_details)
    else:
        print('No notification set')

# Further down in the file

def send_notification(event):
    # Simulate sending notification
    print(f"Notification sent for event: {event['name']}")

if __name__ == '__main__':
    event = {'name': 'Reading Marathon', 'date': '2023-11-12', 'notify': True}
    schedule_event(event)
----------------

I can see the print statements when I run the file, but no actual notification is being sent (I’m simulating it with a print call). Do you have any suggestions on what might be going wrong or how to add debug logging to understand the flow better?
